==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lupercalia
<hw>Lu`per*ca"li*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luperealis</ets>, fr. <ets>Lupercus</ets> the Lycean Pan, so called
fr. <ets>lupus</ets> a wolf, because he kept off the wolves.]</ety>
<fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A feast of the Romans in honor of
<persfn>Lupercus</persfn>, or Pan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lupine</ent>⟦br⟧
